{"body": "I don't know if the idea is that modules like ActiveRecord::Timestamp can be used outside of ActiveRecord::Base (which depends on ActiveModel, which adds #initialize_dup).\r\n\r\nIf ActiveRecord::Timestamp is used outside of ActiveRecord::Base, then it could be possible that the method doesn't exist in case of Ruby 1.8.\r\n\r\nIn Ruby 1.8 there is some sort of implicit assumption that the method was defined somewhere else. Not sure if it's a real problem, though.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9563813", "created_at": "2012-10-18T13:16:52Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7371#issuecomment-9563813", "updated_at": "2012-10-18T13:16:52Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7371, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/csmuc", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2b4e5507d94dc84a187d35c2884c0f3d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe5085f260c2bc7e50f153bd3d3a463d9.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2b4e5507d94dc84a187d35c2884c0f3d", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "csmuc", "type": "User", "id": 16403, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/csmuc/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523def17bd354364b900b98e"}, "id": 9563813, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7371"}
